75 minutes + 1 GB data + 200 MB whatsApp data  – R199 MTN <img class="size-full wp-image-357911 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MTN.png" alt="" width="640" height="401" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MTN.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MTN-300x188.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> MTN said that its Black Friday deals will go live at 00h01 on Friday (29 November) and will run through until Monday (2 December). While MTN has been secretive about its deals, it has hinted at some of the specials on offer including: Apple deals – starting from R699
Samsung deals – from R329
Huawei deals – from R259 Rain <img class="size-full wp-image-357909 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-2.png" alt="" width="640" height="447" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-2.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-2-300x210.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Rain has unveiled its Black Friday 2019 special, where clients get a free Huawei 5G CPE worth R3,450 with a new Rain 5G subscription. This means that new Rain 5G subscribers will not pay any upfront fees when they sign up. Rain officially launched its 5G service on 11 November, offering unlimited data at speeds of up to 700Mbps at R1,000 per month. Rain’s 5G service is currently available in areas in Johannesburg and Tshwane – where it has around 250 towers – with an estimated 500,000 households in the coverage area. Telkom <img class="size-full wp-image-357913 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Telkom-1.png" alt="" width="640" height="327" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Telkom-1.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Telkom-1-300x153.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Telkom will launch its Black Friday deals on 29 November. Ahead of the launch, the group is running a Black Friday competition where customers can win a projected prize of 500GB mobile data. To enter the competition, Telkom customers must provide their details so that they can receive notifications about Telkom’s Black Friday deals when they launch. Each entry into this competition will contribute 50MB towards the winner’s data pool, and Telkom believes this will culminate in about 500GB of data being given to the winner. At the time of publishing, the data prize pool was 240GB. As part of the data prize, Telkom will also be providing the winner with a Huawei B525 4G router. Vodacom <img class="size-full wp-image-357907 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Vodacom.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Vodacom.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Vodacom-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Vodacom has revealed new Black Friday 2019 deals, which include a massive discount on a 20GB data deal. The mobile operator offers customers savings of up to 75%, with deals that are headlined by a 20GB data contract add-on priced at R175 per month. This package can be bolted on to any existing Vodacom contract and is a 24-month contract add-on product. Other Black Friday deals include laptop and Wi-Fi router bundles, TV and Wi-Fi router combos, smartphone contracts, and an Xbox One bundle. Read: Car and motoring Black Friday deals from Ford, Kia, Hyundai and more 